As checked in the following page
- https://confluence.atlassian.com/servicedesk021/configuring-jira-service-desk-notifications-693896343.html#ConfiguringJIRAServiceDesknotifications-Configuringnotificationsforaproject

It has a sentence about: 
*If the Notifications setting for JIRA Service Desk is disabled, the JIRA notification scheme works as defined for all events and users (including customers).*

Notice that this can be very tricky since the Notification Scheme will only have effect for the users who have access to JIRA, so *only* customers who have access to JIRA (member of jira-user) will be affected by this (Usually, the faced scenario is customers only able to log in through Customer Portal
).

